      • readMapStringSetFromFile

        public java.util.Set<java.util.Set<java.lang.String>> readMapStringSetFromFile(java.lang.String inputDir,
                                                                      java.lang.String fileName,
                                                                      java.lang.String delim1,
                                                                      java.lang.String delim2,
                                                                      java.lang.String delim3)
        Parameters:
        inputDir -
        fileName -
        delim1 - ^
        delim2 - ,
        delim3 - #
        Returns:
        It is used to read the feature sets non-binary-combination rules from txt file. The rules are kept in the format: Individual Event^Maximal Repeat, Tandem Repeat#Super Maximal Repeat, Tandem Repeat#Super Maximal Repeat, Tandem Repeat which has the meaning individual event can be mixed with {Maximal Repeat, Tandem Repeat},{Super Maximal Repeat, Tandem Repeat}, and { Maximal Repeat, Tandem Repeat}, i.e. the possible combinations are {Individual Event,Maximal Repeat, Tandem Repeat},{Individual Event, Super Maximal Repeat, Tandem Repeat}, and {Individual Event, Maximal Repeat, Tandem Repeat}
